name: Air Fryer Cauliflower
ingredients:
1 cup panko bread crumbs
1 teaspoons smoked paprika
 teaspoon garlic powder
 teaspoon onion powder
 teaspoon cayenne
 heaping teaspoon sea salt
1 large egg
2 cups small cauliflower florets
Extra-virgin olive oil, for drizzling
Lemon wedges, for serving
Tartar Sauce, for serving
directions:
On a rimmed tray, mix the panko, smoked paprika, garlic, onion, cayenne, and salt. In a small shallow bowl, lightly beat the egg.

Preheat the air fryer to 370F.

Dip each cauliflower floret into the egg, coat with the panko mixture, then place onto a large plate. Drizzle the cauliflower with olive oil and place into the air fryer basket in a single layer with a little space between each floret. Dont overcrowd the basket. Work in batches if necessary. Air fry for 9 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown and crisp. Repeat with any remaining cauliflower.

Serve with lemon wedges and tartar sauce.
